Former Liverpool defender Mark Lawrenson believes Brendan Rodgers should select Lucas Leiva in midfield because the Brazilian would add some defensive solidity.

Liverpool have struggled this season to recapture the form that saw them run Manchester City close to last season's Premier League title and currently occupy 11th place in the current standings.

And Lawrenson believes Lucas could be the solution to some of Liverpool’s current problems.

