Former Liverpool defender Mark Lawrenson insists that Brendan Rodgers should select Lucas in midfield

‘Lucas is generally a 7/10 player. He isn’t going to change games, but he rarely lets you down and he knows his job,’ Lawrenson wrote in his Liverpool Echo column.

‘And if you are a team struggling for form, if you get enough 7/10 performances then you have a chance of changing from bad to good.’

Liverpool have struggled to dominate proceedings in midfield this season with Lukas restricted to three starts this term.

